The inter-ministerial team that was tasked by President Cyril Ramaphosa to go on a fact-finding mission in the North West province is expected to make an announcement about its findings on Wednesday. The team led by Minister in the Presidency Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma, presented its report regarding embattled North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo to Cabinet on Wednesday last week. The team engaged with different sectors in the province. It was appointed by President Ramaphosa to establish facts on the ground and to assess the state of governance in the province following weeks of violent protests by community members calling for Mahumapelo to resign. Following these, an ANC provincial executive committee (PEC) meeting last week. placed Mahumapelo on a “leave of absence” and appointed MEC Wendy Nelson as acting premier. Meanwhile, President Ramaphosa has also placed the entire North West provincial government under the administration of the national government. The Task Team comprises of Ministers of Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation, Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs, Health, Public Works, Agriculture and Finance as well as the Justice, Crime and Prevention Cluster of Ministers. Prior to the announcement, the Ministerial Task Team will also hold stakeholder engagements in Lichtenberg in the Ditsobotla Local Municipality in the North  West. -Afro Reporter